The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks for move evaluation in the game of Go, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and game theory (cs.GT). The paper specifically focuses on the use of supervised learning to train the network using a database of human professional games, which is a common approach in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, followed by cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.GT.
